  "descriptionShort": "Upper-bound estimate of the average extent to which citizens support a democratic political system and reject autocratic alternatives. It combines responses across more than one thousand nationally-representative surveys on how desirable citizens find democracy, how they evaluate undemocratic alternatives (such as a strong unelected leader, the army, or religious authorities), and how they assess democratic and autocratic political systems relative to another.",
  "descriptionProcessing": "The variable matches Claassen's variable `supdem_u95`.",
  "type": "float",
